Welcome to the AI Revolution in Sri Lankan Classrooms!

"අනේ මේ AI! ඒකෙන් අපිට මොනවද කරන්න පුළුවන්?"

If this thought has crossed your mind, you're in the right place! Sri Lanka's education system is getting a super boost with AI, preparing us for a tech-savvy future.

It’s not just a buzzword; it’s happening right here, right now. This isn't some distant dream; it's the unfolding reality of how we learn, create, and prepare for the world.

A Quick Rewind

80s

The Pioneers

Figuring out how to get ~2,300 Sinhala glyphs on a computer screen. The audacity of translation.

2000s

Intelligent Systems

University of Moratuwa begins dabbling in early AI. Seeds of the future are sown.

2024

The Boom

AI in school syllabi, tech giant partnerships, and AI Clubs popping up nationwide.

A tutor who knows exactly where you struggle. Bridging the urban-rural gap and making top-notch education accessible to everyone.

02

භාෂා ඉගෙනීම සෙල්ලමක් කරන AI

Perfect your English essays or Sinhala pronunciation with AI coaches like SinLlama and Talkpal.

03

පර්යේෂණ සහ ගෙදර වැඩ වලට වේග බූස්ටරය

Text-to-speech for the visually impaired and virtual science assistants for remote schools. Leveling the playing field.

The Grand Vision

National AI Strategy (2024-2028) aims to make Sri Lanka an AI hub. From Grade 6 to University, we're not just using AI—we're creating it!

Wait, What are we worried about?

The Digital Divide

Ensuring rural areas aren't left behind without laptops or internet.

Copy-Paste Syndrome

Over-reliance on AI harming critical thinking. Plagiarism increased by 40%.

Teacher Training Gap

Moving from "banning AI" to "guiding students to use it wisely."

Privacy Matters

Keeping personal student information safe and private.

The Road to 2030

01

Universal Internet Access (2025)

Aiming for every school to be connected as part of the Digital Transformation policy.

02

Localized AI Ecosystem

More sophisticated Sinhala and Tamil AI tools building on SinLlama.

03

Ethics-First Integration

Strong focus on responsible use, fairness, and administrative automation.

Embracing AI, the Sri Lankan Way

AI is a powerful tool, not a magic wand, and certainly not a replacement for our amazing teachers! It's here to assist, enhance, and inspire.

"Let us not mistake the instrument for the orchestra, or the tool for the craftsman."

Let's learn to use it wisely and responsibly!
